  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Launch app, open 1-1 chat, send or request ether -> \"Recipient address must be specified\" error. On second attempt it works as expected\r\n![screenshot_20170706-141001](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/27910571-60dd7250-625e-11e7-8041-77c74811a2a3.png)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nCan send/request ether \r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nsend or request ether -> \"Recipient address must be specified\" error.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nvideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=0Bz3t9zSg1wb7bFNtZU1JU1oxMDQ\r\n- Open Status\r\n- open 1-1 chat\r\n- send 0.1 ether -> \"Recipient address must be specified\" error\r\n- send 0.1 ether -> unsigned transactions screen\r\n- request 0.2 ether -> \"Recipient address must be specified\" error\r\n- request 0.2 ether -> request is sent\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.8-63-gb018d8ba+\r\n* Operating System: \r\nReal device Samsung Galaxy S6, Android 6.0.1\r\nReal device iPhone 6s, iOS 10.2.1\r\n\r\n",
